properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, first Pacific survey flight from California to Hawaii; blue stamped “First flight” cachet at right; postmarked April 22, 1935 in Honolulu and April 23, 1935 in San Francisco over three 3-cent stamps; no backstamp.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “April 1935 - Pan American survey flight - Honolulu to San Francisco”, and black and white photographic image of Pan American Sikorsky S-42 on water.
